text.tspan: Prevalence of undernourishment vs. daily supply of calories, 2013
The prevalence of undernourishment, defined as the share of the total population with caloric intakes which fall below
minimum energy requirements, versus the daily supply of calories in kilocalories per person per day. Due to data
reporting, countries with an undernourishment prevalence of '2.5%' includes those of '2.5% and below'.
Source: UN Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO)
